      "content": "At the molecular level, the reaction starts with the condensation of the amino group from an amino acid onto the carbonyl group of a reducing sugar, forming a unstable intermediate. This intermediate then undergoes a series of complex dehydration and rearrangement reactions, leading to the formation of melanoidins and various volatile flavor compounds. These complex polymers, melanoidins, are the large molecules responsible for the deep brown color you observe.",
